text: Kulbayevo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kyzyl-Yarsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 339 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 25 km from Yermekeyevo, 7 km from Suyemetovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Yermekeyevsky District
title: Kulbayevo
